FBIS4-43568 "drweu118_i_94009" FBIS-WEU-94-118 Daily Report 19 Jun 1994 FRANCE RPF Rejects French Presence in Rwanda RPF Rejects French Presence in Rwanda LD1906220594 Paris Radio France International in French 2130 GMT 19 Jun 94 LD1906220594 Paris Radio France International French BFN [Excerpts] The French ambassador to the United Nations will officially submit the draft plan for the creation of a humanitarian intervention force to the Security Council tomorrow morning. [passage omitted] The French proposal is not meeting unanimous approval: The Rwandan Patriotic Front [RPF] is repeating this evening that it will not hear of French soldiers in Rwanda. It has even refused to listen to Jean-Michel Marlaud, the French ambassador to Rwanda, who has been given the task of contacting all the sides quickly. Paul Kagame, the RPF military head, has just said that he will not meet Jean-Michel Marlaud. [passage omitted]
